            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains two notebooks that belonged to Reverend Jesse B. Norviel.</p>
                                 <p>Norviel was pastor of the United Brethren in Christ Church in Urbana, Illinois, and served as Itinerant and Superintendent of the United Brethren&#039;s Lower Wabash Conference from 1915 to 1916. The Lower Wabash Conference was a supervisory body that oversaw United Brethren in Christ churches in eastern Illinois and western Indiana.</p>
                                 <p>The notebooks document his work as Conference Superintendent, a position in which he oversaw ministry at churches in the conference. One notebook consists primarily of financial information such as travel expenses and pastors&#039; contracts and salaries. It also contains lists such as &quot;pastors to be&quot; and licenses granted. The other notebook, which is missing fifty of its pages, contains a list of lay delegates and other brief notes.</p>
                                 <p>Dennis F. Walle purchased the notebooks at an estate sale of Ethel Lemay, Norviel&#039;s daughter, and donated them to the Illinois Historical Survey, predecessor to the Illinois History and Lincoln Collections, in 1973.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


